Articles.Content:
When Loading KSP, latest version of ModuleManager 3.0.0 gives me an error when loading? (nothing else seems to happen yet) and it points out to this file: \GameData\InterstellarFuelSwitch\PatchManager\CDT7Setups.cfg

Anyone else having the same error? What should this mean?
This is what it is inside that file:

Spoiler

PatchManager
{
    modName = InterstellarFuelSwitch
    patchName = CDT7Setups
    srcPath = InterstellarFuelSwitch/PatchManager/PluginData/CDT7Setups.cfg
    shortDescr = CDT: 7 Fuel Setups
    longDescr = Cryogenic Dual Tanks can store LFO, MethaLOx, HydroLOx, HydroOxi, Liquid Fuel, Liquid Methane and Liquid Hydrogen.
//    dependencies =
    exclusions = CDT4Setups,CDT12Setups
//    icon = InterstellarFuelSwitch/icons/stuff
    installedWithMod = true
//    author = Eleusis La Arwall
}

I think that It is calling for this InterstellarFuelSwitch/PatchManager/PluginData/CDT7Setups.cfg But there is no such file in that folder. There are only two files there. I redoanloaded IFS but it is the same.

Edited December 5, 2017 by Agustin
Did you delete the ModuleManager cache files in your GameData?
I have the same error msg, but the file exists and game crashs in VAB, unless I delete IFS.

edit the file and remove all ":FOR[WarpPlugin]" in it

On ‎06‎/‎12‎/‎2017 at 12:26 AM, DoctorDavinci said:

Did you delete the ModuleManager cache files in your GameData?

 

MM deletes the cache files and wont create a new one if it finds an error
